# Evaluator rubric

> The maker-checker yardstick. A **checker** pass (or subagent) grades finished feature work
> against this — separate from the harness audit, which only checks *structure*.
> A feature can't go ✅ in `FEATURES.md` until every `must` row passes.
> Every criterion must be mechanically confirmable. If a checker can't verify it, reword it.

## Grade each feature

| # | Criterion | Level | How the checker confirms it |
|---|-----------|:-----:|-----------------------------|
| 1 | `Done when` criteria all met | must | Re-read the feature's criteria; each maps to a proof |
| 2 | Build passes | must | `{{VERIFY_BUILD}}` → `HARNESS_VERIFY: PASS` |
| 3 | Tests pass (where applicable) | must | `{{VERIFY_TEST}}` → PASS, count didn't silently drop |
| 4 | Evidence recorded | must | Feature's evidence sub-table is filled, not `Pending` |
| 5 | In scope | must | `git diff` touches only files this feature should — no drive-by edits |
| 6 | Constitution honored | must | No rule in `CONSTITUTION.md` violated |
| 7 | No new dead code | should | Deletions traced; no orphaned symbols left (repo-wide grep) |
| 8 | Verified in the real runtime | should | Exercised where the change is user-visible |

## Verdict

- **PASS** — every `must` holds → feature may be marked ✅.
- **REWORK** — any `must` fails → back to the maker with the failing rows named.
- **CONDITIONAL** — all `must` pass but a `should` is deferred → mark 🟠 and name what's
  pending. Never silently skip it.
